(male). A, wing; B, hypopygium; C, antenna; D, coxa and femur I; E, femur II.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="9C7FA31503020900FCEBB52DCC40CDA5" blockId="38.[806,1025,1407,1429]" box="[806,1025,1407,1429]" pageId="38" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="AEB47F0703020900FCEBB52DCB3FCDA4" box="[806,894,1407,1428]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="65">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C7FA31503020900FCEBB5FFCB3CCE31" blockId="38.[806,1421,1453,1537]" pageId="38" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="AEB47F0703020900FCEBB5FFCBE2CDF2" box="[806,931,1453,1474]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="65">Etymology.</emphasis>
Refers to the robust appearance (stout, compact body shape, relatively short legs) of this species.
</paragraph>
